# Package Manager and Next.js Commands

## Use pnpm for package management

When installing packages, always use pnpm instead of npm or yarn.

```
# Instead of
npm install <package>
yarn add <package>

# Use
pnpm add <package>
```

For development dependencies:

```
# Instead of
npm install --save-dev <package>
yarn add --dev <package>

# Use
pnpm add -D <package>
```

For running scripts:

```
# Instead of
npm run <script>
yarn <script>

# Use
pnpm <script>
```

## Next.js Commands

For Next.js operations, use the following commands:

```
# Development server
pnpm dev

# Build for production
pnpm build

# Start production server
pnpm start

# Linting
pnpm lint
```

## Global Commands

For global package installations:

```
# Instead of
npm install -g <package>
yarn global add <package>

# Use
pnpm add -g <package>
```